page.title: 10St. Sennen Church.
page.content: {Sennen Church}was founded by the Irish {St. Senan}in 520 A.D. It was built in the fifteenth or fourteenth century.It is relatively small.It has a{font}and an{organ}with 29 pipes.There have been tales of{ghosts}of different people but no_one has ever seen anything.The tower is 16 and a half metres high.It is a 3 staged tower containing{six {bells. The stone spiral steps go all the way to the top.One{club}is held in the church which is bellringing.In the grave yard there is a grave from the eighteenth century.Also buried there is{Dionyus William}who died in 1775.He was a keen astronomer.Sennen church has a letter from{Charles}1,thanking his Cornish loyalists for helping him in the Civil War.
